cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper focuses on few-shot learning from visual examples and verbal descriptions, which suggests that it could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category, as the paper deals with visual learning and uses the miniImageNet benchmark, which is commonly used in computer vision research. 

cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also likely, as the paper discusses the role of verbal descriptions in few-shot learning. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also possible categories, as the paper deals with machine learning techniques and AI systems. 

cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is less likely, but still possible, as the paper may involve neural network models for few-shot learning.
